    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="24"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867n.404Wailing Wall/27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-26T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 26, 1929—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British authorities sent armed convoy Hebron today to evacuate Jewish
                    noncombatants guarded in Hebron police barracks. British authorities promised to
                    evacuate Americans and I sent Simon, Jewish <pb facs="0168" n="50"
                        xml:id="pg_50"/> member of the consulate general, with a convoy to obtain
                    list of names of all American citizens, including dead and wounded, and to
                    assist evacuation of the living. All Americans are now evacuated except 14
                    students and 2 others who refused to leave without the other students, but it is
                    hoped to secure their evacuation tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
